PROGRAM 7 : What can be done using one type of loop can also be done using the other two types of loops : True / False ? 

ANSWER : TRUE 

------------------------------------------------------------

EXPLANATION :

In Java, there are three main types of loops :

1) for loop
2) while loop
3) do-while loop

All three loops are used to perform repetition (iteration).

Any task that can be done using a for loop can also be done 
using a while loop or a do-while loop.

The difference between them is only in :

• Syntax
• Readability
• Condition checking position

------------------------------------------------------------

KEY DIFFERENCE :

1) for loop
   - Used when number of iterations is known.
   - Condition is checked before execution.

2) while loop
   - Used when number of iterations is not known.
   - Condition is checked before execution.

3) do-while loop
   - Executes at least one time.
   - Condition is checked after execution.

------------------------------------------------------------

EXAMPLE :

Print numbers from 1 to 5 using different loops.

Using for loop :

for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    System.out.println(i);
}

Using while loop :

int i = 1;
while (i <= 5) {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
}

Using do-while loop :

int i = 1;
do {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
} while (i <= 5);


CONCLUSION :

All three loops can perform the same logical operations.
Only the structure and usage style are different.
