PROGRAM 9 : A do while loop is executed : 
            a) At least once
            b) At least twice
            c) At most once

ANSWER : a) At least once ✅

------------------------------------------------------------

EXPLANATION :

A do-while loop executes the loop body first,
and then checks the condition.

This means the statements inside the loop
are executed at least one time,
even if the condition is false.

------------------------------------------------------------

SYNTAX :

do {
    // statements
} while (condition);

------------------------------------------------------------

EXAMPLE :

public class Loops {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int i = 10;

        do {
            System.out.println("Hello");
        } while (i < 5);
    }
}

------------------------------------------------------------

OUTPUT :

Hello

------------------------------------------------------------

WHY ?

In this example, the condition (i < 5) is false
because 10 is not less than 5.

But still, "Hello" is printed once
because the do-while loop checks
the condition after executing the loop body.

------------------------------------------------------------

CONCLUSION :

A do-while loop is always executed at least once,
regardless of whether the condition is true or false.
